- cs.SP (Speech Processing): Although not explicitly mentioned in the abstract, frequency estimation is also a common problem in speech processing, which falls under the signal processing umbrella.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses neural networks as the main tool for frequency estimation, which could potentially fall under the neural and evolutionary computing sub-category.
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the problem of estimating the number of frequencies in addition to their values, which could potentially involve information-theoretic concepts.
